descr: "Resource to define constraints on the Expansion of a FHIR ValueSet."

fields.name: resourceType
fields.descr: "This is a ExpansionProfile resource"

fields.name: url
fields.descr: "An absolute URI that is used to identify this expansion profile when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This SHALL be a URL, SHOULD be globally unique, and SHOULD be an address at which this expansion profile is (or will be) published. The URL SHOULD include the major version of the expansion profile. For more information see [Technical and Business Versions](resource.html#versions)."

fields.name: _url
fields.descr: "Extensions for url"

fields.name: identifier
fields.descr: "A formal identifier that is used to identify this expansion profile when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance."

fields.name: version
fields.descr: "The identifier that is used to identify this version of the expansion profile when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the expansion profile author and is not expected to be globally unique. For example, it might be a timestamp (e.g. yyyymmdd) if a managed version is not available. There is also no expectation that versions can be placed in a lexicographical sequence."

fields.name: _version
fields.descr: "Extensions for version"

fields.name: name
fields.descr: "A natural language name identifying the expansion profile. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation."

fields.name: _name
fields.descr: "Extensions for name"

fields.name: status
fields.descr: "The status of this expansion profile. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content."

fields.name: _status
fields.descr: "Extensions for status"

fields.name: experimental
fields.descr: "A boolean value to indicate that this expansion profile is authored for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing), and is not intended to be used for genuine usage."

fields.name: _experimental
fields.descr: "Extensions for experimental"

fields.name: date
fields.descr: "The date  (and optionally time) when the expansion profile was published. The date must change if and when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the expansion profile changes."

fields.name: _date
fields.descr: "Extensions for date"

fields.name: publisher
fields.descr: "The name of the individual or organization that published the expansion profile."

fields.name: _publisher
fields.descr: "Extensions for publisher"

fields.name: contact
fields.descr: "Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher."

fields.name: description
fields.descr: "A free text natural language description of the expansion profile from a consumer's perspective."

fields.name: _description
fields.descr: "Extensions for description"

fields.name: useContext
fields.descr: "The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These terms may be used to assist with indexing and searching for appropriate expansion profile instances."

fields.name: jurisdiction
fields.descr: "A legal or geographic region in which the expansion profile is intended to be used."

fields.name: fixedVersion
fields.descr: "Fix use of a particular code system to a particular version."

fields.name: excludedSystem
fields.descr: "Code system, or a particular version of a code system to be excluded from value set expansions."

fields.name: includeDesignations
fields.descr: "Controls whether concept designations are to be included or excluded in value set expansions."

fields.name: _includeDesignations
fields.descr: "Extensions for includeDesignations"

fields.name: designation
fields.descr: "A set of criteria that provide the constraints imposed on the value set expansion by including or excluding designations."

fields.name: includeDefinition
fields.descr: "Controls whether the value set definition is included or excluded in value set expansions."

fields.name: _includeDefinition
fields.descr: "Extensions for includeDefinition"

fields.name: activeOnly
fields.descr: "Controls whether inactive concepts are included or excluded in value set expansions."

fields.name: _activeOnly
fields.descr: "Extensions for activeOnly"

fields.name: excludeNested
fields.descr: "Controls whether or not the value set expansion nests codes or not (i.e. ValueSet.expansion.contains.contains)."

fields.name: _excludeNested
fields.descr: "Extensions for excludeNested"

fields.name: excludeNotForUI
fields.descr: "Controls whether or not the value set expansion includes codes which cannot be displayed in user interfaces."

fields.name: _excludeNotForUI
fields.descr: "Extensions for excludeNotForUI"

fields.name: excludePostCoordinated
fields.descr: "Controls whether or not the value set expansion includes post coordinated codes."

fields.name: _excludePostCoordinated
fields.descr: "Extensions for excludePostCoordinated"

fields.name: displayLanguage
fields.descr: "Specifies the language to be used for description in the expansions i.e. the language to be used for ValueSet.expansion.contains.display."

fields.name: _displayLanguage
fields.descr: "Extensions for displayLanguage"

fields.name: limitedExpansion
fields.descr: "If the value set being expanded is incomplete (because it is too big to expand), return a limited expansion (a subset) with an indicator that expansion is incomplete, using the extension [http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/valueset-toocostly](extension-valueset-toocostly.html)."

fields.name: _limitedExpansion
fields.descr: "Extensions for limitedExpansion"
